description: The index tracks the performance of the exchange-listed equities of companies across the globe that engage in Real Estate Technology Business. The adviser generally expects to use a replication strategy. A replication strategy is an indexing strategy that involves investing in the securities of the index in approximately the same proportions as in the index. The fund will invest at least 80% of its net assets in companies that derive a majority of their revenues or profits from Real Estate Technology Business. It is non-diversified.
